HEADWORD: Trifling
<hw>Tri"fling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being of small value
or importance; trivial; paltry; <as>as, a <ex>trifling</ex> debt; a
<ex>trifling</ex> affair.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Tri"fling*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Tri"fling*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

